casebody.data:
ROBERT PALMER, Plaintiff and Respondent, v. DANIEL KELLY, Defendant and Appellant.

Before Freedman, Curtis, and Van Vorst, JJ.

Decided June 28, 1873. E. Brown, for appellant. L. A. Fuller, for respondent.

Opinion by Curtis, J. Freedman and Van Vorst, JJ., concurred.

Appeal from a judgment in favor of plaintiff, and from an order denying a new trial.

Action for the taking and conversion of personal property.

Judgment and order affirmed.
